This proof is obligatory for all works contracts. However, no approval is required for works contracts classified in a category or subcategory whose value is less than EUR 75,000 and EUR 50,000 respectively.

In order to be able to carry out a public works contract, the contractor must meet a number of conditions. If he meets them, he receives approval from the competent regional minister, following the opinion of the Federal Approval Commission. These conditions relate primarily to :
- technical capacity ;
- financial capacity;
- professional integrity.

The contractors are divided into :
- classes, according to the scope of the work they can carry out ;
- categories and/or sub-categories according to the specific nature of the work.
